"'''The Last One Standing'''" is a short story written by [[Jude Watson]] and appearing in the [[Legacy of the Jedi/Secrets of the Jedi omnibus|''Legacy of the Jedi/Secrets of the Jedi'' omnibus]].

==Plot summary==
[[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] is contemplating the death of [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], though still feeling as if he were alive in some way. Later, Obi-Wan is monitoring the [[Lars homestead/Legends|Lars homestead]] to protect the infant [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. However, when [[Owen Lars/Legends|Owen]] and [[Beru Whitesun Lars/Legends|Beru Lars]] discover that the [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Sand People]] have stolen twenty of their [[Moisture vaporator/Legends|moisture vaporators]], Owen decides to gather together a group of fellow [[Moisture farmer/Legends|moisture farmers]] to battle the fearsome Sand People.

Obi-Wan, not wanting Luke's protective "father"-figure to die as he surely would, decides to track the Sand People on his own. He eventually tracks them down by following their tracks, while contemplating his memories of Anakin, and then a group of uli-ah back to their camp. Things go well there for a while: he finds the vaporators in the Sand People's tents and loads them onto a [[Bantha/Legends|bantha]].

However, as he's about to leave, he is spotted by a lone Tusken Raider, who attacks him. Though Obi-Wan disarms him easily, the Raider then howls, which alerts all the other [[Gender/Legends|males]] in the camp that they have an intruder. They all attack him, and Obi-Wan slowly starts to hate them, causing him to slip to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] slightly before he hears the voice of [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]], which brings him back to the [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light]]. Instead of murdering the entire clan as Anakin had done in the past, Obi-Wan cuts their clothes off to reveal their skin&mdash;a taboo to the Sand People, which would usually result in the others of their tribe murdering them. This gives him time to escape on the bantha with the vaporators and causes him to become a legend for the Sand People.

On returning to the Lars homestead, Obi-Wan is met with an icy welcome, where Owen informs him that they did not need his help.

